{
  "stem": "2004.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But if you're packed in, 100 people in a cattle car, there really is no consideration.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "You-- you just look out for yourself and try to be-- try to be as-- as-- try to disturb your next door neighbor as little as possible.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But you look out for yourself and try to survive.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were all trying to sort of-- and this father, he was a husky man.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he-- he desperately tried to help this-- this little boy of his.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now I don't know what has happened to them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I know that when we arrived in Mauthausen, that child never, ever survived.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because in Mauthausen, there were no children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So anyway, we arrived in Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] We are at Mauthausen maybe no more than two days.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, we get an order to be loaded up into cars all over again.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We are loaded up into cars.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now this is already-- we are probably in August of 1943.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we are getting shipped.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And what do we know?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We don't know where we're being shipped.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now this time, as bad as it was coming from Plaszow to Mauthausen, it was worse leaving Mauthausen, because we were in the mountains there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was even hotter.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And again, it took us seven days.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were shipped to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we arrive in Auschwitz seven days later.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, at the time, I think that from that train, there were several dead people in that train that never made it anymore, because we-- we-- it was-- it was absolutely horrendous.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That ride back from Mauthausen to Auschwitz was even worse-- if it is imaginable, it was even worse than the ride from Plaszow to Mauthausen, which was bad enough.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
